 The correlation between average wind and wind turbines location can be
 visually inspected from Figure 4 (as well as appendix figure 3).
 The figure makes it evident that wind turbines (depicted as black triangles)
 tend to be placed in areas characterized by higher wind level (dark-shaded).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Column 4 of Table 1 shows that zip codes with and without a wind turbine
